FBIS4-5905 "dreas073_d_94013" FBIS-EAS-94-073 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 South Korea PRC Friendship Pact Report Officially Denied PRC Friendship Pact Report Officially Denied SK1504060894 Seoul YONHAP in English 0600 GMT 15 Apr 94 SK1504060894 Seoul YONHAP English BFN [Text] Seoul, April 15 (YONHAP) -- South Korea on Friday officially denied press reports that it has consulted with China on signing a bilateral friendship treaty. Responding to press reports that Seoul offered to sign the pact at ongoing policy planning talks in Beijing, Foreign Ministry spokesman Chang Ki-ho said, "the proposal was made just as an idea and it cannot be considered that we had any talks or consultations with Beijing on the matter." The press had reported that Seoul proposed signing the treaty at the Beijing talks which opened Wednesday and that China responded positively to the offer.
